g.text: TickerTest
Phase 0 –Preparation for implementation
Contracts signed between practices and iPlato/TickerTest
TickerTestprovide training to general practice staff (if appropriate)
OHID provide other training materials to general practice staff
Practice search for and identify eligible patients
Eligible patients’ NHS numbers are extracted from practice system and sent to iPlato
T&Cs agreed by general practice for iPlato to access patient records
iPlato creates unique user IDs for each patient and shares information with TickerTest
Tickertest creates a user account for each patient and returns this information to iPlato
Phase I –Implementation of Digital NHSHC
iPlato invite eligible patients for digital NHSHC
Patient agrees to digital NHSHC
Patient does not respond
Patient starts but does not complete digital NHSHC
Patient completes digital NHSHC
Patient provides details for receipt of home blood test kit
Patient collects sample and returns to MMH
Tickertest receives sample results from MMH
iPlato writes back data into patient record
iPlato notifies practice via email
iPlato send reminder invitation (up to 2)
Patient declines invitation
TickerTestnotifies practice, OHID, LA, CHAD of uptake
NHSHC data sent to iPlato
iPlato upload invitation materials to system
Practice selects a random subsample of eligible patients for invite
iPlato reminds patient to complete digital NHSHC (up to 2 reminders to complete outstanding actions)
